ce:section.ce:para:
Four QCM sensors were prepared and coated with the various carbon-based materials according to the details given in the Experimental section, and labeled as follows: GNP, CNT, GNP-CNT, and GNP-CNT-CQD. To compare their performance, the response of the coated sensors against various concentrations of ethanol (100 to 7500 ppm) was recorded at room temperature. Each sensing cycle involve 5 min exposure to the detected analyte, followed by a 5 min pure nitrogen purging to reset to the sensor's baseline (Fig. 6
                        ). The results presented in Fig. 7
                         demonstrate a significant improvement in sensitivity for the hybrid CNT-GNP composite when compared to its individual components. At a concentration of 500 ppm, the CNT-GNP composite exhibited response increases of approximately 1466 % and 970 % compared to the GNP and CNT sensors, respectively. These percentage differences decreased at higher concentrations, which can be attributed to the saturation of the sensing film in the case of the CNT-GNP composite. Nevertheless, the CNT-GNP sensor still displayed response enhancements of approximately 284 % and 106 % compared to the GNP and CNT sensors, respectively, when detecting ethanol at a concentration of 7500 ppm. The significant enhancement in the response of the hybrid CNT-GNP composite is attributed to its novel three-dimensional structure, which can significantly reduce the expected agglomeration in the case of individual components. Upon examining the CNT-GNP-CQD hybrid composite's response, the presence of CQDs had a modest effect on sensor response, ranging from 1 % to 8 %, when compared to that of the CNT-GNP composite. However, this effect was consistently observed across all concentration levels (from 500 ppm to 7500 ppm). These results suggest that CQDs could be further utilized in the development of sensors for various systems, potentially enhancing the response factor at low analyte concentrations. This could be very useful in future sensor development studies.
